name: pytables

pre_pr_migrator_status.pypy37: not solvable: master: ['linux_aarch64_numpy1.19python3.7.____73_pypy: Encountered problems while solving.\nProblem: nothing provides openssl >=1.0.2p,<1.0.3a needed by python-3.6.7-hd21baee_1002\n']

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "3.7.0" %}

package:
  name: pytables
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/t/tables/tables-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: e92a887ad6f2a983e564a69902de4a7645c30069fc01abd353ec5da255c5e1fe
  patches:
    - do_not_copy_dlls_into_package.patch

build:
  number: 3
  entry_points:
    - pt2to3 = tables.scripts.pt2to3:main
    - ptdump = tables.scripts.ptdump:main
    - ptrepack = tables.scripts.ptrepack:main
    - pttree = tables.scripts.pttree:main
  skip: true  # [py<35]

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cython                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    # If blosc is not in the build environment, PyTables setup.py will work
    # around it by using it's own internal version of computational libraries
    # (see c-blosc/internal-complibs). These internal libraries may not match
    # the conda environment versions and may cause segfaults.
    - blosc
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - cython
    - numpy
    - zlib
    - lzo  # [linux]
    - bzip2
    - hdf5
    - numexpr
    - blosc
    - packaging
  run:
    - python
    - six
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - numexpr
    - packaging

test:
  requires:
    - setuptools
  commands:
    - pt2to3 -h
    - ptdump -h
    - ptrepack -h
    - pttree -h


about:
  home: http://www.pytables.org
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Brings together Python, HDF5 and NumPy to easily handle large amounts of data.
  description: |
    PyTables is a package for managing hierarchical datasets and designed to
    efficiently and easily cope with extremely large amounts of data. PyTables
    is built on top of the HDF5 library, using the Python language and the
    NumPy package.
  doc_url: http://www.pytables.org/
  dev_url: https://github.com/PyTables

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - msarahan
    - ocefpaf
    - tomkooij
    - scopatz
    - avalentino
